# Frontend Rules

## Component patterns
- Use functional components with hooks (no class components)
- State management via React Context (AppContext, AuthContext, DataContext)
- Navigation via `useApp().navigateTo(viewId)` — no router library
- Data fetching via `useData()` hook (wraps databricksData.js API calls)

## Styling
- Tailwind CSS v4 utility classes only
- Brand colors as arbitrary values: `text-[#1A1A1A]`, `bg-[#F5C400]`, etc.
- No gradients, no shadows heavier than `shadow-sm`
- Keep it clean, light, professional — reference: Linear, Vercel Dashboard

## UX principles (from HANDOFF-BRIEF)
- Zero learning curve — obvious at first glance
- One thing per screen — single clear purpose
- Show, don't ask — smart defaults ("This Week", "My Branch")
- Use domain language: "Comments" not "Enrichment", "Zone" not "Region"

## Before editing any component
1. Read the component file fully
2. Check what imports it (grep for the component name)
3. Understand the data flow (props, context, selectors)
4. Make the minimal change needed

## API date contract (critical)
- Never pass raw JavaScript `Date` objects into query params.
- For API date filters (`start_date`, `end_date`), always serialize to `YYYY-MM-DD` using a shared helper (e.g., `toApiDate`).
- `buildQuery` callers must pass already-normalized date strings.
